Ethiopian runners showed class on Saturday; winning the men and women’s categories of the 7th edition of the Access Bank Lagos City Marathon. While Ulfata Gelata claimed the first position in the men’s race, his compatriot Dagne Siranesh Yirga finished ahead of all the other runners in the women’s category. Geleta who finished as the first runner-up at last year’s edition moved up this time to emerge as the proud winner of the $30,000 first price money. Though the Ethiopian’s winning time of 2.11.54 sec was short of the Course Record set in the 2020 edition,  it is the second-fastest ever in the history of the annual 42km road race. The Kenyan duo of  David Barmasai and Emmanuel Naibei settle for second and third places respectively.   Sanwo-Olu: Marathon embodies spirit of Lagos     Osimhen shines as Napoli hold Inter     KIFA signs MOU with Ilaji Hotels and Sports Resort   - Advertisement - Barmasai and Naibei went home with $20,000 and $15,000, respectively for their efforts at this year’s race. In the women category, Ethiopia’s Dagne winning time was 2 hours 33 minutes and 50 seconds. She was followed in second place by compatriot Alemenseh Guta and Kenya’s Naomi Maiyo in third place. This is only the second time that an Ethpionan will win both the male and female categories of the Access Bank Lagos City Marathon. In the Nigeria category, Shehu Muazu and Fadekemi Olukemi were the top finishers who won the N1m prize monies set aside for the indigenous athletes. SPONSORED